commit.message: Ripple extended errors back up
Updated versions

Multiple cleanups and some potential bug fixes.
Fixed hidden bug in pldstr where testing of pointer instead of char.

Clean up some compiler warnings
Greatly expanded maximumn array sizes for MIME_headers fixed allocations

Fixed multivalue/multipart header reconsolidation.
Some multipart header name/filename entries were not being correctly
decoded due to whitespace.

Improved the MIMEH_recompose_multivalue() call to handle quoted segments.

commit.message:
Allow TAB after line break

This is backed up by the following references

When unfolding, WSP should be ignored. (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5322#section-2.2.3)
WSP =  SP / HTAB ; white space (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5234#appendix-B.1)

Update MIME_headers.c

Added a generic _strcasestr() function so that we don't have to rely on the libs on the system, as sometimes ripMIME is built on rather obscure systems and not all will support the strcasestr() call.  MIMEH_strcasestr() could be further optimised but in this case it's probably not warranted.
pull up the next line in MIMEH_fix_header_mistakes only if it doesn't start with Content-Type to avoid failing to extract attachments from some malformed messages
